PRD / SRS DOCUMENT
Product Name

GreenPulse

One-Line Description

A real-time environmental compliance interpretation system that converts live PM2.5 sensor data into regulator-ready compliance events using Pathway, with all enforcement actions remaining manual.

Problem Statement

Environmental sensors generate continuous air-quality data, but regulatory compliance checks are typically performed on periodic (monthly/quarterly) reports. This delay causes violations to be discovered after environmental and health damage has already occurred.

Root Gap:
Continuous data × periodic compliance = delayed enforcement.

Objective

Build a Pathway-powered streaming system that:

Continuously evaluates live PM2.5 data

Applies zone-specific regulatory rules

Distinguishes transient spikes from violation candidates

Produces decision-ready compliance events

Keeps all enforcement actions fully manual

Target User

Primary: Environmental Compliance Officers (Pollution Control Boards)

Functional Requirements

FR1: Ingest live (simulated) PM2.5 data from 2–3 stations

FR2: Compute rolling time-window metrics

FR3: Apply zone-based regulatory rules

FR4: Classify events as OK / TRANSIENT / VIOLATION

FR5: Generate LLM-based explanations

FR6: Mark all events as PENDING_OFFICER_REVIEW

Non-Functional Requirements

Real-time streaming (no batch jobs)

Deterministic demo behavior

CLI-only output

Explainability over prediction

Pathway as the core engine (mandatory)

Out of Scope

Dashboards / UI

Sensor hardware

Enforcement automation

Fine calculation

Authentication / payments

Databases